'''Rotraut Richter''' (15 May 1915 – 1 October 1947) was a German [[stage actor|stage]] and [[film actress]]. She appeared in the role of Gerda in the 1933 [[Nazi]] [[propaganda film]] ''[[Hitlerjunge Quex (film)|Hitlerjunge Quex]]'', receiving a letter of thanks from [[Joseph Goebbels]] along with the rest of the cast.<ref>Kreimeier p.206-7</ref>

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[The First Right of the Child]]'' (1932)
* ''[[Hitlerjunge Quex (film)|Hitlerjunge Quex]]'' (1933)
* ''[[The Sporck Battalion (1934 film)|The Sporck Battalion]]'' (1934)
* ''[[Don't Lose Heart, Suzanne!]]'' (1935)
* ''[[Fruit in the Neighbour's Garden (1935 film)|Fruit in the Neighbour's Garden]]'' (1935)
* ''[[Trouble Backstairs (1935 film)|Trouble Backstairs]]'' (1935)
* ''[[The Violet of Potsdamer Platz]]'' (1936)
* ''[[Meiseken]]'' (1937)
* ''[[The Beaver Coat (1937 film)|The Beaver Coat]]'' (1937)
* ''[[Somewhere in Berlin]]'' (1946)
* ''[[Wozzeck (film)|Wozzeck]]'' (1947)

